node.title: Flash flooding warnings issued as storms lash Melbourne, state's north
node.alt: Picture of lightning across grey sky.
node.description: Residents in some parts of Melbourne are being warned not to enter flood waters as slow-moving storms pelt the city with heavy rain and hailstones and lead to road closures.
node.content: ["Residents in parts of Melbourne have been warned they may be in danger of localised flash flooding as heavy rain\u00a0pelts the city.", "Watch and Act alerts have been\u00a0issued\u00a0for Preston, Essendon, Footscray, Caroline Springs and surrounding areas as slow-moving storms sweep across the suburbs.", "Some roads have been closed and VicRoads has reported\u00a0flooding\u00a0in areas including Dudley Street at\u00a0West Melbourne and\u00a0Footscray Road at Docklands.", "Emergency services have warned those in the affected areas not to enter\u00a0floodwaters and to move indoors.", "The Bureau of Meteorology has issued severe thunderstorm warnings for damaging winds, large hailstones and heavy rainfall for people in parts of the Central, Mallee and Northern Country areas.", "Wind gusts of\u00a0up to 106kph have\u00a0been recorded at Melbourne Airport.", "The bureau said\u00a0the thunderstorms were detected near Camberwell, Caulfield, Footscray, Melbourne City, Preston, Ringwood, St Albans and Sunbury.", "They are forecast to shift to\u00a0Craigieburn, Doncaster and Mill Park and later to Belgrave, Greensborough and to the west of Whittlesea.", "More to come."]
